How to Commit ,Push & Pull From GitHub

sudo su
yum update -y
yum install git -y
mkdir <foldername>
cd <foldername>
git init
ls -a ( to check git local repo create .git)
git remote add origin https://github.com/Dnyaneshwar4298/DevOps.git
touch Devops-notes
cat >Devops-notes
git status 
git add Devops-notes
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

->> Next Topic is How to use ignore Command <<-

To ignore some files while commiting :- 

Create one hidden file (.ignore) and enter file format which you want to ignore

For Example:-  
vi .ignore
*css
*java

->> git add .ignore
->> git commit -m "massage which you want to give"
->> git status

Create some files text java,css files and add them by running git add command.

For example :-
touch sample.txt 
touch testing.java

->> ls 
->> git add .
->> git status 
->> git commit -m "massage which you want to give"
